<head>
<title>Town Hall Job Opening</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<h2><center>Town Hall Job Opening</H2></center>
<hr>
<h3><center>Account Representative</h3></center>
Town Hall, the first conservative on-line community, has an opening for an account representative.  The ideal candidate will live in the Washington, DC area and have:
<ul>
<li>1-2 years of proven sales experience
<li>knowledge of and experience with the conservative movement
<li>the ability to work independently
<li>computer skills (on-line knowledge a plus)
<li>strong writing and communication skills
<li>BA/BS degree
</ul><p>
Please see below for a job description.  If you feel you meet these requirements, e-mail a cover letter, resume, and salary history to <a href="mailto:annk@townhall.com">annk@townhall.com</a>
<p>
OR, fax the materials to 202-544-7330.<br>
<p>
<p>
<h4>DESCRIPTION:</h4>
Meet or exceed quota responsibility for group sales of Town Hall.  Working closely with marketing team, develop comprehensive sales strategies to service existing Town Hall accounts and recruit new ones. <br>
<p>
<h4>RESPONSIBILITIES:</h4>
<ul>
<li><b>New Sales:</b>  Reach a specified quota of sales to new organizations each month through telephone contacts, daily meetings, prospecting, and other contacts.<br>
<li><b>Service Existing Accounts:</b>  Keep in close contact with current organizations to answer questions, ensure Town Hall's contractual obligations are fulfilled, furnish regular "hits" reports, and suggest enhancements.<br>
<li><b>Conferences:</b>  Attend internal and external conferences to demonstrate products and make new contacts.<br>
<li><b>Market Research:</b>  Keep marketing team informed of competitive information, new services, etc.<br>
<li><b>Reports/Files:</b>  Submit regular call and reimbursement reports to manager.  Maintain complete files on all prospects and clients.<br>
</ul>
<BR><HR WIDTH="30%"><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/heritage/hbut.map"><IMG SRC="/heritage/hbut.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A></CENTER></body>
</html>

