<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Frank Gregorsky</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="ship.gif" WIDTH="87" HEIGHT="80" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"
ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER>
<H2><CENTER>Frank Gregorsky<BR>
<I>Fellow<BR>
</I><IMG SRC="barrwb.gif" WIDTH="512" HEIGHT="5" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"></CENTER>
</H2>
Frank Gregorsky is a writer and editor who has the ability to write about
almost anything from a conservative, future-friendly viewpoint. From November
1981  to July 1983 he served<IMG SRC="grgrsky.jpg" WIDTH="96" HEIGHT="121"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN="RIGHT"> as Rep. Newt Gingrich's Chief of Staff
and in 1985 took a position as a staff writer under the Reagan Administration
in the White House Communication Dept. Later he was the Special Projects
Director for the House Republican Conference. Currently he spends his time
running Gregorsky Editorial Services. Gregorsky also has long time experience
in political publishing.<BR>
<BR>
Besides having numerous articles published over the years in such publications
as <I>The Wall Street Journal, New York Times, National Review, Washington
Post, Christian Science Monitor, Roll Call, </I>and<I> Crisis</I>, he was
the editor of the Republican Study Committee Bulletin (1983 - 1985), The
House Republican (1986- 1988), and Asst. Editor of Invest-Net Inside (1992).
<BR>
