<H1><CENTER>EVERYONE'S TALKING ABOUT SAM BEARD'S REVOLUTIONARY BOOK ON RESCUING
SOCIAL SECURITY</CENTER>
</H1>
<P><CENTER><IMG SRC="rwbline2.gif" WIDTH="512" HEIGHT="6" ALIGN="BOTTOM"
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"></CENTER>
<H4><CENTER>&quot;This book will help frame the debate for the 1996 presidential
campaign.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<I>William Kristol, The Weekly Standard</I><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
&quot;...if we do not plan for the future, entitlement spending promises
will exceed financial resources in the next century. The current spending
trend is clearly unsustainable. In this creative book, Sam Beard lucidly
identifies some <BR>
of the problems in our Social Security system and proposes <BR>
innovative ways to solve them.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<I>United States Senator (D) Bob Kerry </I><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Sam Beard's call for a national grassroots debate on these issues
is so vitally important for the future of the Social Security program. Beard
offers Americans a fresh, outside-the-beltway approach which deserves our
most serious and conscientious consideration.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<I>United States Senator (R) Alan K. Simpson</I><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Sam Beard has devised the unassailable substitute for the Social Security
system, which even the AARP would approve of. Why didn't we think of it?&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<I>William F. Buckley, Jr.</I><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Sam Beard offers a creative plan to remodel Social Security for the
21st century while upholding that contract with today's seniors. ... His
plan not only protects seniors and ensures retirement security for future
generations, but promises economic growth and keeps the American Dream alive.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<I>Sandra L. Butler, President United Senior Association</I><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
&quot;As Social Security hurdles towards insolvency, Sam Beard offers an
innovative approach that might enable America to stave off entitlement collapse
and provide future generations with a vibrant retirement system. His recommendations
deserve serious analysis and consideration.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<I>Richard Thau, Jonathon Karl, Douglas Kennedy, Third Millennium</I><BR>
<BR>
<BR>
&quot;Restoring Hope in America brings the looming Social Security crisis
to our attention - and presents a unique and thoughtful solution worth discussing!
... Everyone should read Restoring Hope in America and get involved in the
debate about Social Security.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
<I>Dorcas Hardy, Former U.S. Commissioner of Social Security</I></CENTER>
