<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Endangered Species Act</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><H3><I>From the Fall 1995 Discovery Journal:</I></H3><H1><CENTER>Plumbing the Endangered Species Act </CENTER></H1><BR>Does the following paragraph sound familiar? <DL><DD><B>&quot;Traditionally, species, subspecies, and populations have beenplaced on the (Endangered Species) list when their numbers are too low tomanage effectively. The result is a death watch as species decline and geneticvariability diminishes. ... (S)pecies should be placed on the threatenedlist early enough to allow time to manage them before they become endangered.By focusing conservation on threatened species, the severe regulatory constraintsof the Endangered Species Act can be largely removed. Only when a speciesis approaching the point where management options become limited are regulatorycontrols necessary for species conservation.&quot;</B> </DL>It's actually from a working draft of the Endangered Species ManagementAct, sponsored by Sen. Dirk Kempthorne (R-Idaho), subcommittee chairmanof the Senate Environment and Public Works Committee. But the sentimentis totally in the spirit of Noah's Choice, by Discovery Senior Fellow MarkL. Plummer and Charles C. Mann (Knopf, 1995). We don't write legislationat Discovery, but we are delighted when those who do use our ideas! <BR><BR>With his co-author &quot;Cam&quot; Mann, Plummer recently also attractedwhat was described as the largest audience of legislators to show up atthe Caucus (about 100). Democratic as well as Republican members said theyare reading <I>Noah's Choice</I>. On the same visit, Plummer and Mann met,at his invitation, with Rep. Richard Pombo (R- California), co-sponsor withRep. Don Young (R-Alaska) of the House ESA reform act. <BR><HR><H3><CENTER><A HREF="ilsjrn.html">Discovery Journal Fall 1995 Table of Contents</A><BR><A HREF="journal.html">Discovery Journal</A><BR><A HREF="views.html">Discovery Views</A><BR><A HREF="inquiry.html">Discovery Inquiry</A></CENTER></H3><P><CENTER><BR><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="discoimg.gif" WIDTH="173" HEIGHT="73" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN=bottom></A></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
